### ğŸ”§ **3. Compile Nagios**

* âœ… `sudo make all`

---

### ğŸ‘¤ **4. User & Group Setup**

* âœ… `sudo make install-groups-users`
* âœ… `sudo groupadd -r nagios` *(only if not created above)*
* âœ… `sudo passwd nagios`
* âœ… `sudo usermod -aG nagios www-data`

---

### ğŸ“‚ **5. Install Core Files**

* âœ… `sudo make install`

---

### ğŸ”„ **6. Set Up Nagios as a Service**

* âœ… `sudo make install-daemoninit`
* âœ… `sudo make install-commandmode`
* âœ… `sudo make install-config`
* âœ… `sudo make install-webconf`

---

### ğŸŒ **7. Apache Configuration**

* âœ… `sudo a2enmod cgi`
* âœ… `sudo a2enmod rewrite`
* âœ… `sudo htpasswd -c /usr/local/nagios/etc/htpasswd.users nagiosadmin`

---

### ğŸ” **8. Verify & Restart**

* âœ… `sudo /usr/local/nagios/bin/nagios -v /usr/local/nagios/etc/nagios.conf`
* âœ… `sudo systemctl restart nagios`
* âœ… `sudo systemctl restart apache2`

---

### ğŸ§© **9. Nagios Plugins Installation**

* âœ… `sudo apt-get install -y automake autotools-dev bc build-essential dc gawk gettext libmcrypt-dev libnet-snmp-perl libssl-dev snmp`
* â• Then:

```bash
